Here is the complete code implementing the `peek_data_from_buffer` function.

This implementation relies on the standard behavior of dynamic buffers (similar to Boost.Asio or C++ Networking TS), where `buffer.data()` returns a sequence of memory blocks (a `ConstBufferSequence`). We iterate through these blocks to copy the requested number of bytes into a vector without calling `consume()`, ensuring the read pointer remains unchanged.

```cpp
#include <hexi/dynamic_buffer.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>
#include <algorithm> // Required for std::min

template<size_t block_size = 1024>
std::vector<uint8_t> peek_data_from_buffer(const hexi::dynamic_buffer<block_size>& buffer, size_t bytes_to_peek) {
    // 1. Determine the actual number of bytes to read.
    // We cannot peek more data than what is currently available in the buffer.
    size_t actual_size = std::min(bytes_to_peek, buffer.size());

    // 2. Prepare the destination vector with the required capacity.
    std::vector<uint8_t> result;
    result.reserve(actual_size);

    // 3. Get the underlying buffer sequence.
    // dynamic_buffer::data() returns a ConstBufferSequence. Since 'buffer' is const,
    // this view is read-only and does not modify the read position.
    // The data might be split across multiple non-contiguous memory blocks.
    auto buffer_sequence = buffer.data();

    size_t remaining = actual_size;

    // 4. Iterate through the buffer sequence to copy data.
    for (const auto& buf : buffer_sequence) {
        if (remaining == 0) {
            break;
        }

        // Get the size of the current memory block
        size_t chunk_size = buf.size();

        // Determine how many bytes to copy from this specific block
        // (either the whole block or just enough to finish the request)
        size_t to_copy = std::min(chunk_size, remaining);

        // Get the pointer to the raw data
        const uint8_t* data_ptr = static_cast<const uint8_t*>(buf.data());

        // Append the data to the result vector
        result.insert(result.end(), data_ptr, data_ptr + to_copy);

        // Update the remaining count
        remaining -= to_copy;
    }

    return result;
}
```

