Here is the complete code implementing the in-place endianness conversion functions using the `Hexi` library and C++20 standard features.

The implementation assumes `hexi::byteswap` is the function provided by the library to perform unconditional byte swapping, and uses `std::endian` from `<bit>` to determine when swapping is necessary.

```cpp
#include <hexi/endian.h>
#include <cstdint>
#include <bit>

template<typename T>
void convert_from_big_endian_inplace(T& value) {
    // If the native system is little-endian, we must swap bytes to convert 
    // from big-endian to native (and vice versa).
    if constexpr (std::endian::native == std::endian::little) {
        value = hexi::byteswap(value);
    }
}

template<typename T>
void convert_from_little_endian_inplace(T& value) {
